    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hammers that are fixed on an angle, usually used in forging, and operated by cam-wheels which alternately tilt the hammers upward and let them drop. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
